cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes an algorithm for adapting to unknown magnitudes of target functions, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning and reinforcement learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to Atari 2600 games, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
